<item>
            <title>[LU-19181] interop sanity test_56wc: file data has changed (1): md5sum invalid argument</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-19181</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This issue was created by maloo for Andreas Dilger &amp;lt;adilger@whamcloud.com&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This issue relates to the following test suite run: &lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/470452f2-b812-4f0e-9ba3-0a16eb2284c4&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/470452f2-b812-4f0e-9ba3-0a16eb2284c4&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;test_56wc failed with the following error:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;md5sum: /mnt/lustre/d56wc.sanity/f56wc.sanity: Invalid argument
file data has changed (1)
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Test session details:&lt;br/&gt;
clients: &lt;a href=&quot;https://build.whamcloud.com/job/lustre-master/4615&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://build.whamcloud.com/job/lustre-master/4615&lt;/a&gt; - 5.14.0-427.42.1.el9_4.x86_64&lt;br/&gt;
servers: &lt;a href=&quot;https://build.whamcloud.com/job/lustre-b2_15/100&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://build.whamcloud.com/job/lustre-b2_15/100&lt;/a&gt; - 4.18.0-553.27.1.el8_lustre.x86_64&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It looks like this has failed interop testing 100% with b2_15 servers and master clients since 2025-03-14 and was passing 100% before 2025-03-06:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.whamcloud.com/search?client_branch=master&amp;amp;server_branch=b2_15&amp;amp;horizon=15552000&amp;amp;test_set_script_id=f9516376-32bc-11e0-aaee-52540025f9ae&amp;amp;sub_test_script_id=24b24afa-b8f6-11e7-8afb-52540065bddc&amp;amp;source=sub_tests#redirect&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.whamcloud.com/search?client_branch=master&amp;amp;server_branch=b2_15&amp;amp;horizon=15552000&amp;amp;test_set_script_id=f9516376-32bc-11e0-aaee-52540025f9ae&amp;amp;sub_test_script_id=24b24afa-b8f6-11e7-8afb-52540065bddc&amp;amp;source=sub_tests#redirect&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It doesn&apos;t look like it relates to kernel versions on the client and server, so it is likely related to a landing at that time. &lt;/p&gt;





